# Widgets and CaravaggioUI — [[project_name]]

## CaravaggioUI (required)

This project uses `caravaggio_ui` **1.0.6**. Initialize in `main.dart` via `CaravaggioUI.initialize(...)`.

```dart
import 'package:caravaggio_ui/caravaggio_ui.dart';
```

**Component catalog:** read `docs/architecture/CARAVAGGIO_COMPONENTS.md` before creating or editing presentation UI.

Prefer CaravaggioUI components over raw Material widgets when equivalents exist (see catalog mapping table).

## Pages — CustomScaffold (required)

All routed pages **must** use `CustomScaffold` from `lib/widgets/common/custom_scaffold.dart`.

- Do **not** use Material `Scaffold` + `AppBar` on pages.
- `showBackButton: false` on root routes: Home, Splash, Login.
- `showBackButton: true` on all other pages (add-page, feature pages, nested routes).
- Use `bodyBuilder` with `topPadding` for scrollable content.
- Move toolbar actions (add, refresh) to the `action` slot — no `FloatingActionButton`.

```dart
import 'package:caravaggio_ui/caravaggio_ui.dart';
import 'package:[[project_name]]/widgets/common/custom_scaffold.dart';

CustomScaffold(
  title: CText.title('Title', size: TextSize.small),
  showBackButton: true,
  body: ...,
);
```

Reusable BLoC **components** (`*_component.dart`) do **not** include a scaffold — the parent page provides `CustomScaffold` and `BlocProvider`.

## Widget locations

| Type | Path | Use when |
|------|------|----------|
| App-wide shared | `lib/widgets/common/` | Scaffold, loading, error, empty states — **reuse first** |
| Cross-feature component | `lib/features/components/<name>/` | Reusable UI with its own BLoC (list/single/form) |
| Feature-local | `lib/features/<feature>/presentation/widgets/` | Widget used only in one feature |
| Pages | `lib/features/<feature>/presentation/*_page.dart` or `lib/features/<name>/<name>_page.dart` | Routed screens |

## Existing shared widgets

| Widget | Path | Implementation |
|--------|------|----------------|
| `CustomScaffold` | `lib/widgets/common/custom_scaffold.dart` | Wraps `CScaffold` |
| `LoadingWidget` | `lib/widgets/common/loading_widget.dart` | `CLoader.bouncing()` |
| `ErrorWidget` | `lib/widgets/common/error_widget.dart` | `CText.body` |
| `UnknownStateWidget` | `lib/widgets/common/unknown_state_widget.dart` | `CText.body` |

Import with `package:[[project_name]]/widgets/common/...`.

## Reuse policy

1. Check `lib/widgets/common/` before creating loading/error UI or page shells.
2. Check `lib/features/components/` before building similar list/form UIs.
3. Extract to `features/components/` when a second feature needs the same UI.
4. Keep feature-specific layout in `presentation/widgets/`.
5. Consult `CARAVAGGIO_COMPONENTS.md` before introducing new Material widgets.

## Presentation patterns

- `BlocBuilder` with typed `switch` on Freezed states.
- Use `ErrorLocalizer` for failure messages.
- `MultiBlocProvider` with explicit `List<SingleChildWidget>` typing.
- Lists: `CTile.simple` instead of `ListTile`.
- Loading: `LoadingWidget` or `CLoader` instead of `CircularProgressIndicator`.

